  {
    "name": "aggregate_ontology_objects",
    "title": "aggregate_ontology_objects",
    "description": "Perform comprehensive aggregation functions on object fields in the specified ontology and object type.\n\n## Supported Aggregation Functions:\n\n- **count**: Count the number of objects (no field required)\n- **sum**: Sum numeric values across objects\n- **avg**: Calculate average of numeric values\n- **min**: Find minimum value in a field\n- **max**: Find maximum value in a field\n- **approxDistinct**: Approximate count of distinct values (faster than exact)\n\n## Field Name Resolution\n\nField names in aggregations, groupBy, and where clauses are automatically resolved. You can use either:\n\n- **propertyApiName** (e.g., `rcaStatus`) — the API name from `view_foundry_object_type` output's `apiName` field\n- **propertyTypeId** (e.g., `rca_status`) — the property key from `view_foundry_object_type` output\n\nThe tool loads the object type metadata and translates propertyTypeIds to the correct API names before querying. If a field name is not found as a propertyTypeId, it is passed through as-is (assumed to already be an API name).\n\nSimilarly, `objectTypeApiName` accepts either the object type's API name (e.g., `RpsIncident`) or its object type ID (e.g., `rps-incident`). The tool resolves the correct API name automatically.\n\n## Limitations\n\n- **Edit-only properties**: Properties not backed by a dataset column (edit-only properties) do not support groupBy or field-based aggregations (avg, sum, min, max). A basic count without groupBy will still work.\n- **Stream-backed object types**: Object types backed only by streams may have limited aggregation support.\n- **Workaround**: For object types with these limitations, use `run_sql_query_on_foundry_dataset` to run SQL aggregation queries directly against the backing dataset.\n\n## Advanced Features:\n\n- **Grouping**: Group results by one or more fields using the groupBy parameter\n- **Filtering**: Apply where clause to filter objects before aggregation\n- **Accuracy Control**: Choose between EXACT (precise) or APPROXIMATE (faster) calculations\n- **Result Naming**: Assign custom names to aggregation results using the `name` field\n\n## Example Use Cases:\n\n### Basic Count\n\n```json\n{\n    \"ontologyRid\": \"ri.ontology.main.ontology.12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012\",\n    \"objectTypeApiName\": \"Employee\",\n    \"aggregations\": [{ \"type\": \"count\", \"name\": \"totalRecords\" }]\n}\n```\n\n### Sales Analytics by Region\n\n```json\n{\n    \"ontologyRid\": \"ri.ontology.main.ontology.12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012\",\n    \"objectTypeApiName\": \"Sale\",\n    \"aggregations\": [\n        { \"type\": \"sum\", \"field\": \"revenue\", \"name\": \"totalRevenue\" },\n        { \"type\": \"avg\", \"field\": \"revenue\", \"name\": \"avgRevenue\" },\n        { \"type\": \"count\", \"name\": \"salesCount\" }\n    ],\n    \"groupBy\": [{ \"type\": \"exact\", \"field\": \"region\" }],\n    \"where\": {\n        \"type\": \"and\",\n        \"value\": [\n            { \"type\": \"gte\", \"field\": \"revenue\", \"value\": 1000 },\n            { \"type\": \"eq\", \"field\": \"status\", \"value\": \"completed\" }\n        ]\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Employee Performance Summary\n\n```json\n{\n    \"ontologyRid\": \"ri.ontology.main.ontology.12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012\",\n    \"objectTypeApiName\": \"Employee\",\n    \"aggregations\": [\n        { \"type\": \"avg\", \"field\": \"salary\", \"name\": \"avgSalary\" },\n        { \"type\": \"min\", \"field\": \"salary\", \"name\": \"minSalary\" },\n        { \"type\": \"max\", \"field\": \"salary\", \"name\": \"maxSalary\" },\n        { \"type\": \"approximateDistinct\", \"field\": \"skillSet\", \"name\": \"uniqueSkills\" }\n    ],\n    \"groupBy\": [{ \"type\": \"exact\", \"field\": \"department\" }],\n    \"accuracy\": \"REQUIRE_ACCURATE\"\n}\n```\n\n### Multi-dimensional Analysis\n\n```json\n{\n    \"ontologyRid\": \"ri.ontology.main.ontology.12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012\",\n    \"objectTypeApiName\": \"Order\",\n    \"aggregations\": [\n        { \"type\": \"count\", \"name\": \"orderCount\" },\n        { \"type\": \"sum\", \"field\": \"totalAmount\", \"name\": \"revenue\" }\n    ],\n    \"groupBy\": [\n        { \"type\": \"exact\", \"field\": \"customerType\" },\n        { \"type\": \"exact\", \"field\": \"orderDate\" }\n    ],\n    \"where\": {\n        \"type\": \"or\",\n        \"value\": [\n            { \"type\": \"eq\", \"field\": \"priority\", \"value\": \"high\" },\n            { \"type\": \"gte\", \"field\": \"totalAmount\", \"value\": 5000 }\n        ]\n    },\n    \"accuracy\": \"ALLOW_APPROXIMATE\"\n}\n```\n\n## Parameter Definitions\n\n- **ontologyRid**: The unique identifier for your Foundry ontology (format: `ri.ontology.main.ontology.{UUID}`)\n- **objectTypeApiName**: The API name of the object type to aggregate (e.g., \"Employee\", \"Sale\", \"Order\"). Also accepts the object type ID (e.g., \"employee\", \"sale\").\n- **aggregations**: Array of aggregation functions to perform on the data\n- **groupBy**: Optional array of grouping clauses to organize results\n- **where**: Optional filter query to limit which objects are included\n- **accuracy**: Optional accuracy level (`REQUIRE_ACCURATE` for precise results, `ALLOW_APPROXIMATE` for faster processing)\n\n## Advanced Grouping Examples\n\n### Time-Based Grouping (Duration)\n\n```json\n{\n    \"ontologyRid\": \"ri.ontology.main.ontology.12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012\",\n    \"objectTypeApiName\": \"Event\",\n    \"aggregations\": [{ \"type\": \"count\", \"name\": \"eventsPerMonth\" }],\n    \"groupBy\": [\n        {\n            \"type\": \"duration\",\n            \"field\": \"createdAt\",\n            \"value\": 1,\n            \"unit\": \"MONTHS\"\n        }\n    ]\n}\n```\n\n### Numeric Range Grouping (Fixed Width)\n\n```json\n{\n    \"ontologyRid\": \"ri.ontology.main.ontology.12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012\",\n    \"objectTypeApiName\": \"Product\",\n    \"aggregations\": [{ \"type\": \"count\", \"name\": \"productsPerPriceRange\" }],\n    \"groupBy\": [\n        {\n            \"type\": \"fixedWidth\",\n            \"field\": \"price\",\n            \"fixedWidth\": 100\n        }\n    ]\n}\n```\n\n### Custom Range Grouping\n\n```json\n{\n    \"ontologyRid\": \"ri.ontology.main.ontology.12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012\",\n    \"objectTypeApiName\": \"Employee\",\n    \"aggregations\": [{ \"type\": \"avg\", \"field\": \"salary\", \"name\": \"avgSalaryByAgeGroup\" }],\n    \"groupBy\": [\n        {\n            \"type\": \"ranges\",\n            \"field\": \"age\",\n            \"ranges\": [\n                { \"startValue\": 18, \"endValue\": 30 },\n                { \"startValue\": 30, \"endValue\": 50 },\n                { \"startValue\": 50, \"endValue\": 65 }\n            ]\n        }\n    ]\n}\n```\n\n## Search Query Reference\n\n### Text Search Operations\n\n```json\n{\n    \"where\": {\n        \"type\": \"containsAllTerms\",\n        \"field\": \"description\",\n        \"value\": \"machine learning model\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAvailable text search types:\n\n- `containsAllTerms`: All terms must be present\n- `containsAllTermsInOrder`: All terms in specified order\n- `containsAllTermsInOrderPrefixLastTerm`: Ordered terms with prefix matching on last term\n- `containsAnyTerm`: Any of the terms present\n- `startsWith`: Field starts with value\n- `wildcard`: Pattern matching with wildcards\n\n### Null and Array Operations\n\n```json\n{\n    \"where\": {\n        \"type\": \"and\",\n        \"value\": [\n            { \"type\": \"isNull\", \"field\": \"deletedAt\", \"value\": false },\n            { \"type\": \"contains\", \"field\": \"tags\", \"value\": \"priority\" }\n        ]\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Comparison Operations\n\nAll standard comparison operators are supported:\n\n- `eq`: Equal to\n- `gt`/`gte`: Greater than / Greater than or equal\n- `lt`/`lte`: Less than / Less than or equal\n- `in`: Value in array\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Accuracy Settings\n\n- **REQUIRE_ACCURATE**: Use for financial calculations, compliance reports, or when exact numbers are critical\n- **ALLOW_APPROXIMATE**: Use for dashboards, trend analysis, or large datasets where speed matters more than precision\n\n### Optimization Tips\n\n1. **Large Datasets**: Use `ALLOW_APPROXIMATE` with `approximateDistinct` for better performance\n2. **Time Series**: Use duration-based grouping instead of exact grouping for time fields\n3. **Complex Queries**: Use specific filtering to reduce processing overhead\n4. **Filtering**: Apply `where` clauses to reduce data before aggregation\n",
    "inputSchema": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "ontologyRid": {
          "type": "string",
